-- Blankfein Says Wall Street Has `a Lot of Work to Do' to Regain Confidence
-- Dan Reichl
-- 2010-04-28T02:17:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-28/blankfein-says-wall-street-has-a-lot-of-work-to-do-to-regain-confidence.html

          
          
             Goldman Sachs Group Inc. Chief
Executive Officer Lloyd Blankfein said Wall Street firms have
“a lot of work to do to regain the confidence of Main Street.”
He spoke in a Bloomberg Television interview today after
testifying before U.S. lawmakers in Washington.  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     Lloyd C. Blankfein, chairman and chief executive officer of Goldman Sachs Group Inc., speaks during an interview after testifying at a Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs subcommittee hearing on Wall Street and the financial crisis, in Washington, D.C., on April 27, 2010. Photographer: Joshua Roberts  
                           

     
